---
import PageShell from '../components/layout/PageShell.astro';
---

<PageShell
  title="US State"
  description="State and local AI policy activity. Coverage is in development."
>
  <article class="container-narrow us-state prose">
    <p class="us-state__kicker meta">STATE</p>
    <h1>State &amp; local coverage</h1>
    <p class="us-state__lead">
      State and local AI policy coverage is planned. This page is a
      placeholder while the data pipeline and scope rules are being
      designed.
    </p>
    <p>
      The intent mirrors the federal side: a neutral ledger of pending and
      resolved activity, sourced from official publications, with the same
      conservative keyword scope. Rows will link out to the authoritative
      source rather than hosting detail pages.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you have a state or city whose AI activity you think belongs here,
      or a data source we should be reading, suggestions are welcome on
      GitHub.
    </p>
  </article>
</PageShell>

<style>
  .us-state {
    padding-block: var(--sp-10) var(--sp-12);
  }
  .us-state__kicker {
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0 0 var(--sp-3);
  }
  .us-state h1 {
    font-size: var(--fs-3xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-5);
  }
  .us-state__lead {
    font-size: var(--fs-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-5);
  }
</style>
